In a statement issued by the National Security Advisor General James L. Jones, he reflects on his personal experiences with Senator Edward Kennedy during the early 1980s when he was a young Senate Liaison officer. General Jones praises Senator Kennedy and his staff for being strong supporters of the Marine Corps and always making time for important issues concerning Marines and their families. He credits Senator Kennedy for his instrumental role in passing significant legislation such as Goldwater-Nichols and military pay reforms, which brought about comprehensive reforms in the military and defense establishment. General Jones highlights Senator Kennedy's genuine care and compassion for the men and women in uniform, as well as his fair and open-minded approach during committee hearings. He also acknowledges the ongoing contributions of many of Senator Kennedy's former staff members to the nation.